WEBVTT

00:00.867 --> 00:02.134
Kids, in the fall of 2010,

00:02.135 --> 00:03.402
I was hosting my
very first Thanksgiving.

00:03.403 --> 00:05.538
And I wanted it
to be unforgettable.

00:05.539 --> 00:09.942
Instead of stuffing, I'm going
to fill the turkey with...

00:09.943 --> 00:11.661
a slightly smaller turkey.

00:11.662 --> 00:14.080
It's called a Turturkeykey!

00:14.081 --> 00:16.248
- A Turturkeykey?
- Mm-hmm.

00:16.248 --> 00:19.085
- Uh-uh, oh-oh.
- Yeah, I was there for

00:19.086 --> 00:22.254
the "insertion".
He used shoehorns.

00:22.255 --> 00:23.422
I'll be having sides.

00:24.424 --> 00:26.058
Your loss.
All right, it's dead in here.

00:26.059 --> 00:27.693
I'm gonna call it a little early.

00:27.694 --> 00:29.378
What? No! You can't go now.

00:29.379 --> 00:31.097
It's the night
before Thanksgiving.

00:31.098 --> 00:32.465
College chicks are back in town.

00:32.466 --> 00:33.933
Their moms just made
a snide comment

00:33.934 --> 00:35.468
about the weight they gained.

00:35.469 --> 00:36.602
They called her a bitch,

00:36.603 --> 00:37.937
but deep down,
they know she's right.

00:37.938 --> 00:39.488
And they're about to walk
through that door,

00:39.489 --> 00:40.890
where we will be waiting

00:40.891 --> 00:44.443
with some light beer
and some rock hard approval.

00:44.444 --> 00:46.812
Wh... what u... up?

00:46.813 --> 00:48.447
Yeah. You don't want
to bail early, man.

00:48.448 --> 00:49.649
You could become The Blitz.

00:51.018 --> 00:52.985
Blitz was a guy
we knew in college.

00:52.986 --> 00:54.387
Sadly, he was cursed.

00:54.821 --> 00:55.855
Well...

00:55.856 --> 00:57.256
I'm calling it a little early.

00:57.257 --> 00:59.558
Wh... you sure?
We got big plans.

00:59.559 --> 01:01.827
Yeah. Remember how last week
we fired up a sandwich,

01:01.828 --> 01:03.529
and we listened to Pink Floyd's
Dark Side of the Moon

01:03.530 --> 01:04.964
while watching The Wizard of Oz?

01:04.965 --> 01:05.965
Well, tonight,

01:05.966 --> 01:08.100
we're doing the same thing,

01:08.101 --> 01:10.136
only with "Weird Al"
Yankovic's Greatest Hits

01:10.137 --> 01:11.937
and Apocalypse Now.

01:11.938 --> 01:13.706
We'll see what happens.

01:13.707 --> 01:17.093
Nah, it's Kraft/Croft night:
mac and cheese and Tomb Raider.

01:17.094 --> 01:18.761
Biz-zow!

01:18.762 --> 01:21.213
You see, every time
Blitz left a place,

01:21.214 --> 01:22.481
something amazing happened.

01:26.286 --> 01:27.453
Oh! I'm sorry.

01:27.454 --> 01:29.088
I thought this was my room.

01:31.575 --> 01:34.894
- Completely naked!
- Completely naked!

01:34.895 --> 01:36.362
Aw, man!

01:36.363 --> 01:37.997
And the movie was awesome.

01:37.998 --> 01:39.532
Aw, man!

01:39.533 --> 01:41.300
At the exact moment
Brando first appeared,

01:41.301 --> 01:43.869
"Weird Al" launched
right into "Eat lt."

01:43.870 --> 01:46.038
Aw, man!

01:46.039 --> 01:47.573
And over the years,

01:47.574 --> 01:49.809
"The Curse of The Blitz"
continued.

01:49.810 --> 01:51.677
Well, I'm gonna call it.

01:51.678 --> 01:54.480
I just got Madden 2K1, and
I can't stop thinking about it.

01:54.481 --> 01:55.514
- See you later!
- Bye-bye!

01:55.515 --> 01:56.549
- All right, bye-bye!
- Okay, later!

01:56.550 --> 01:57.750
- Good-bye!
- Bye-Bye!

02:01.254 --> 02:03.723
Tap's broke!
Can't turn 'em off!

02:03.724 --> 02:05.224
Free beer for everyone!

02:07.427 --> 02:09.261
Free beer for everyone!

02:09.262 --> 02:10.763
Free beer for everyone!

02:10.764 --> 02:13.299
Aw, man!

02:14.000 --> 02:15.401
You know what?

02:15.402 --> 02:17.470
Ted, go ahead... leave early
to do something lame.

02:17.471 --> 02:20.473
Just don't blame us
if you become... The Blitz.

02:20.474 --> 02:21.974
All right, first of all...

02:21.975 --> 02:24.810
there's nothing lame
about brining a Turturkeykey,

02:24.811 --> 02:27.079
copyright pending.
And secondly,

02:27.080 --> 02:29.782
I don't believe "The Curse
of The Blitz" is real.

02:29.783 --> 02:32.318
Kids, I'd live
to regret those words.

02:32.319 --> 02:34.253
You see, the "Curse of Blitz"
could be passed

02:34.254 --> 02:36.655
from one person to the next,
at any moment.

02:36.656 --> 02:38.457
Blitz had gotten the curse from
Jerry Windheim,

02:38.458 --> 02:40.893
back in freshman year,
who got it years before that

02:40.894 --> 02:42.428
from Davey Beaterman.

02:42.429 --> 02:43.796
The original Blitz, Matt Blitz,

02:43.797 --> 02:46.165
was a guy who went to Wesleyan
back in the '60s.

02:46.166 --> 02:48.934
He dropped out right before
the school went co-ed.

02:48.935 --> 02:51.203
And then,
Thanksgiving morning...

02:56.276 --> 02:58.177
What the hell happened here?

02:58.178 --> 03:00.246
Hey! Morning, Blitz!

03:00.247 --> 03:02.248
Aw, man!

03:02.249 --> 03:03.999
No, no! Let's get
one thing straight, okay?

03:04.000 --> 03:05.317
I am not The Blitz.

03:05.318 --> 03:09.522
♪ My Blitzy lies
over the ocean ♪

03:09.523 --> 03:13.025
♪ My Blitzy lies
over the sea ♪

03:13.026 --> 03:17.296
♪ My Blitzy lies
over the ocean ♪

03:17.297 --> 03:20.332
- ♪ So bring back my Blitzy... ♪
- Please stop.

03:22.068 --> 03:23.402
Okay, fine.

03:23.403 --> 03:24.770
♪ to me. ♪

03:25.839 --> 03:27.239
The Gentleman!

03:27.240 --> 03:29.875
THE GROUP: - The Gentleman!
- Wait! Wait! Wait!

03:29.876 --> 03:31.043
What's that?
What's "The Gentleman"?

03:31.044 --> 03:33.112
- Oh, you had to be there, Blitz.
- Yes.

03:33.113 --> 03:34.313
I'm not The Blitz!

